06:00.094 --> 06:01.729
Not the specifics, but the tone,

06:01.861 --> 06:04.598
the tone fits.

06:04.732 --> 06:07.034
Erica Shaw, I googled you.

06:07.167 --> 06:08.535
That's not less unsettling.

06:08.736 --> 06:11.305
When I hired you to do
my sister's funeral,

06:11.438 --> 06:13.507
I looked up a few
business reviews online,

06:13.640 --> 06:16.943
but I had no idea my sister
was getting a video send-off

06:17.077 --> 06:19.979
from one of the most
promising new voices

06:20.114 --> 06:22.882
in American documentary. Wow.

06:24.017 --> 06:25.386
What happened?

06:28.622 --> 06:30.090
You googled me.

06:30.290 --> 06:32.202
For the record, there was no
way you could've known that

06:32.226 --> 06:33.960
- that kid was...
- Lotta work.

06:34.094 --> 06:35.462
Excuse me?

06:35.662 --> 06:36.972
I have a lot of work
I have a deadline...

06:36.996 --> 06:38.532
- How did you know?
- What?

06:38.665 --> 06:40.701
The house, red, a frame?

06:40.834 --> 06:43.203
You give me the photos,
I cut everything together

06:43.337 --> 06:44.904
according to aesthetic
continuity...

06:45.105 --> 06:46.973
I was the only one
she told about the affair.

06:47.107 --> 06:49.009
How did you know?

06:52.112 --> 06:53.447
I saw it.

06:53.580 --> 06:54.580
So what?

06:54.648 --> 06:59.086
I saw the... truth,

06:59.219 --> 07:02.356
the thing behind
what everybody else sees.

07:02.489 --> 07:07.761
It just happens sometimes...
Certain people, pictures,

07:07.895 --> 07:10.664
places, I have an instinct or...

07:10.798 --> 07:12.399
A gift.

07:12.533 --> 07:16.804
Isn't that what you used
to call it in interviews.

07:16.936 --> 07:20.474
Yeah. I thought that sounded
real cool when I was 20.

07:20.607 --> 07:24.578
- Until of course...
- Can I point you toward a grief counselor or a therapist

07:24.711 --> 07:28.248
or someone who, I don't know,
isn't in my apartment?

07:28.382 --> 07:31.452
I didn't come here to
talk about my sister.

07:32.753 --> 07:34.922
I have another job for you.

07:35.055 --> 07:36.956
Another dead relative?

07:38.692 --> 07:40.928
I'm sorry, that was...
I was out of line.

07:41.061 --> 07:43.030
A different kind of job,

07:43.163 --> 07:45.599
more in line with
what you used to do.

07:45.732 --> 07:48.135
Not a real documentary,
not yet at least.

07:48.268 --> 07:49.670
But my father,
Campbell Bradford,

07:49.870 --> 07:52.473
has led quite a life,
what I know about it.

07:52.606 --> 07:55.476
He comes from this small
town in Indiana, west baden...

07:55.609 --> 07:57.244
Midwestern,
forgettable, whatever...

07:57.377 --> 07:59.313
I just make funeral
videos now and weddings,

07:59.446 --> 08:01.048
if it's a light month,
that's all.

08:01.248 --> 08:05.252
I figured someone with
your unique skill set

08:05.385 --> 08:09.523
might be able to uncover
a little bit about

08:09.656 --> 08:12.459
- who he was there, his history.
- I'm not the right person.

08:12.593 --> 08:15.562
The advance will cover
as much as you'd make

08:15.696 --> 08:18.632
if you worked every single
day for the next two months.

08:18.765 --> 08:21.568
You should go see him before
you leave for Indiana.

08:21.702 --> 08:23.103
