but you called me

48:31.312 --> 48:33.914
because you wanted...
You wanted to know...

48:35.182 --> 48:36.850
What?

48:37.118 --> 48:39.363
This woman. Okay, yeah.
So you're gonna come down here and what?

48:39.387 --> 48:41.322
You're going to rip
the camera out of my hands?

48:41.588 --> 48:44.392
No, I don't... honey, I don't give
a shit about the rest of the money.

48:44.524 --> 48:46.004
This is my story now, too.
And nobody,

48:46.060 --> 48:47.694
especially not some
north shore bitch,

48:47.827 --> 48:49.829
is gonna stop me from getting...

48:52.266 --> 48:54.567
Fucking entitled...

49:05.512 --> 49:08.049
That fuck has a
family in Chicago?

49:08.182 --> 49:09.462
I'm sorry, I should
have told you

49:09.616 --> 49:10.826
as soon as I knew who you were.

49:10.850 --> 49:13.720
- And he's still alive?
- Yeah.

49:13.853 --> 49:18.558
Yeah, he's got days left,
if that, but he's still...

49:19.759 --> 49:21.995
- Josiah...
- What's he like?

49:24.065 --> 49:25.632
He's...

49:25.765 --> 49:28.868
Old and frail and...

49:30.704 --> 49:32.539
Honestly, it's hard
to imagine him as...

49:32.672 --> 49:33.907
Pure evil?

49:34.808 --> 49:37.445
Yeah.

49:37.577 --> 49:41.449
This guy,
this piece of shit monster,

49:41.581 --> 49:43.550
he terrorizes this place
long before my time

49:43.683 --> 49:45.719
then he just bails.

49:45.852 --> 49:49.556
Starts over.
Pretends it didn't happen.

49:51.359 --> 49:53.893
Well, he fucked up
the whole lot of us

49:54.028 --> 49:55.738
like every branch of
the goddamn family tree

49:55.762 --> 49:57.931
was just snapped in half.

49:59.566 --> 50:01.801
And I'm the only one still here.

50:03.304 --> 50:04.871
Yeah. Why?

50:07.208 --> 50:09.010
The Campbell curse.

50:10.277 --> 50:13.014
They said that shit
like it was a joke.

50:14.415 --> 50:16.117
You know?

50:17.684 --> 50:19.762
Definitely wouldn't mind a few
minutes alone with the guy.

50:19.786 --> 50:23.391
Hop a bus to Chicago.
Tell him to fuck off.

50:23.556 --> 50:25.026
Maybe worse.

50:29.463 --> 50:33.367
At least he made a name
for himself though, right?

50:33.501 --> 50:35.461
Heard he almost bought
this place back in the day,

50:35.535 --> 50:39.773
and here I am fixin' it up
for ten bucks an hour.

50:41.308 --> 50:44.011
You don't think you're
worth more than that?

50:45.612 --> 50:47.181
Do you?

51:05.299 --> 51:07.401
Maybe you can.

51:07.535 --> 51:08.768
What?

51:09.537 --> 51:11.671
Tell him to fuck off.

51:20.214 --> 51:21.815
- You alright?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

51:21.948 --> 51:23.950
- You got this.
- Yeah.

51:25.852 --> 51:26.886
Be ready.

51:27.021 --> 51:28.588
You got somethin' prepared, or...

51:28.721 --> 51:30.291
Just be ready.

51:31.358 --> 51:32.460
Okay.

51:32.592 --> 51:34.295
Let's start with your name

51:34.428 --> 51:36.796
and how you're related
to Campbell Bradford.

51:36.930 --> 51:39.567
Uh, my name is, uh...

51:39.699 --> 51:41.135
Do... am I lookin' at the camera?

51:41.368 --> 51:45.805
Just look at me.
Just a conversation. Easy. Relax.

51:48.175 --> 51:50.743
My name is Josiah Bradford.

51:50.877 --> 51:55.182
Campbell was...
Is my great-grandfather.

51:55.316 --> 51:56.316
And how, would you say,

51:56.417 --> 51:58.486
is your relationship
with Campbell?

51:58.618 --> 52:00.564
Well, I've never... I mean, no, I never...
We already talked about...

52:00.588 --> 52:02.748
- I know. I just need it for context.
- Oh sorry, uh...

52:02.822 --> 52:05.368
- It's alright. How would you say
is your relationship with Campbell?

52:05.392 --> 52:07.061
Never met him.

52:07.194 --> 52:08.862
I mean, ran off
and left his wife

52:08.995 --> 52:10.964
and daughter
long before I was even...

52:13.666 --> 52:15.001
Is this even, I mean...

52:15.202 --> 52:17.002
They're not gonna wanna
hear me say this shit.

52:17.071 --> 52:18.281
Doesn't matter what they want.
What do you want to say?

52:18.305 --> 52:19.540
Why I... this doesn't really...

52:19.672 --> 52:20.940
- Say it.
- What are you...

